programme.title: The Land Of Many Perfumes

programme.title: Whose Baby Is In Classroom?

programme.title: Arjuna In Switzerland
programme.desc: "Arjuna in Switzerland" is a culinary travel show featuring Chef Juna exploring Switzerlands natural beauty and culture, tasting local dishes, and sharing unique experiences.

programme.title: Arjuna In Switzerland
programme.desc: "Arjuna in Switzerland" is a culinary travel show featuring Chef Juna exploring Switzerlands natural beauty and culture, tasting local dishes, and sharing unique experiences.

programme.title: City Of Desire
programme.desc: Sandra returns to Macau after having been in Canada for the last twenty years. Her father is ill and the business is being passed on to her, but she is taken aback to discover that the family business is prostitution.

programme.title: The Goldfinger
programme.desc: Inspired by Hong Kong’s biggest financial scandal in the 1980s, this is a rags to riches story about Ching Yat Yin who is chairman of a listed company. With Ching’s wealth and influence on the rise, ICAC senior investigator Lau Kai Yuen is determined to investigate the case, even if it means spending 15 years in pursuit of the truth.

programme.title: Flashover
programme.desc: This is based on a true story. A sudden earthquake hits the gas pipes in an industrial park, triggering massive explosions and engulfing the neighboring area in flames. When the Fire Rescue Force reaches the scene, firefighters must fight against the flames and time, as they commit to safeguard lives with their own.

programme.title: Reunion Dinner
programme.desc: Chao Yang and Zi Hong are soon to wed but both have not met the others parents. When a client requests for a livestream of their reunion dinner to promote his products, it set the stage for their parents first meeting. Estranged from his mother, Yang decides to rent a family for the dinner which results in a series of mishaps and hilarity.

programme.title: Lost Love
programme.desc: Chan Tin Mei (Sammi Cheng) and Ho Bun (Alan Luk)s son passes away abruptly at just three years old due to congenital heart disease. Suffering in unfathomable pain over the loss, Mei resists having another child. One day, Mei finds out that they can become a foster family.

programme.title: Leio
programme.desc: An ex-singer Kao returns to his hometown for a funeral and takes part in a water drilling contest to save his drought-stricken hometown, as well as to win a million dollar cash prize.

programme.title: Endgame
programme.desc: A killer and a stage actor accidentally swapped their identities at a bathhouse. When the killer strives to become a successful stage actor, he also starts to recall what has happened.

programme.title: Caught In Time
programme.desc: Based on true events, Detective Zhong Cheng leads a task force in pursuit of Eagle, a criminal gang led by Zhang Sun. Highly methodical and disciplined, the gang manages to avoid capture after each heist. A decade later, the need to stop Eagle is more urgent than ever when Zhong Cheng realizes that his time is almost up to solve the case.

programme.title: Detective Dee and Nine-Storey...
programme.desc: A series of strange incidents happen at the Tangs demon building but Detective Dee finds no clue. When the eldest daughter Miss Tang secretly informs Dee about Mr Tangs strange behavior, he vows to unveil the truth.

programme.title: Tales From Occult: Body and Soul
programme.desc: This horror anthology series returns to feature three spooky crime stories about an ex-hair model, a cat lover and the love triangle between a dental nurse, a dentist and a chef.

programme.title: Old Fox
programme.desc: This family drama is about an 11-year-old boy who befriends his landlord, nicknamed Old Fox, and learns from him how to survive in a rapidly changing world as well as things his poor father would never be able to teach him.

programme.title: Wu Xia
programme.desc: Martial artist Liu hides his identity and lives in a remote village with his wife Ah Yu and their two sons, but somehow gets embroiled in a bizarre murder case.

programme.title: Initial D
programme.desc: For five years, 18-year-old Takumi delivers tofu in his fathers near-obsolete Toyota AE86 every morning and because of that, he has become a good racer and also unwillingly perfected the art of drifting.

programme.title: Love Never Ends
programme.desc: An empty-nest elderly man and a widowed elderly woman who collects scrap, meet unexpectedly and gradually develop feelings for each other. An elderly couple whose wife suffers from a serious illness, makes a living by selling scrap. Both these elderly couples fall deeply in love and prove that love never ends, even if there is no tomorrow!

programme.title: Mission Milano
programme.desc: A wealthy entrepreneur goes undercover with an Interpol agent to protect a new invention, the Seed of God, from falling into an international crime conglomerate.

programme.title: I Corrupt All Cops
programme.desc: There was a dark age when corruption and bribery were the order of the day in Hong Kong. One day, comes brave individuals who are determined to end corruption with the founding of Hong Kongs anti-corruption bureau.

programme.title: Chasing The Dragon
programme.desc: Crippled Ho came to Hong Kong as an illegal immigrant in 1963 and ruthlessly carved an empire from the chaotic underworld of drug dealers and corrupt police that ruled the city under notorious detective Lee Rock.

programme.title: My Best Bet
programme.desc: A gambling addict and her anti-gambling husband face relationship challenges when she must return to her old ways after criminals target her family.

programme.title: Keep Rolling
programme.desc: Directorial debut of Man Lim Chung, who spent 3 years filming this documentary about the life and filmmaking philosophy of Ann Hui, one of Hong Kong’s greatest filmmakers. It traces Hui’s life story and her 40-year career’s ups and downs using film footages, candid conversations with Hui, and interviews with her collaborators, family and friends.

programme.title: Schemes In Antiques
programme.desc: When an antique is to be returned to China, Xu Yuan uncovers an ancient mystery and soon embarks on a journey that can finally restore his familys reputation but may also cost him his life.

programme.title: Young And Dangerous: Reloaded
programme.desc: In this remake of “Young and Dangerous”, Chan Ho Nam and his three buddies of the Hung Hing triad gang strive to fight for their own justice, further expanding their power in the triad and becoming a new legend...

programme.title: The Movie Emperor
programme.desc: Actor Lau Wai-Chi has a huge following of devoted followers and is always keeping an eye on his rivals. After accepting to play the lead in a modest indie drama, Lau begins the laborious process of mastering the acting skills for the role.

programme.title: Social Distancing
programme.desc: After seeing a warning video about an e-ghost on YouTube, Cherry begins to encounter many mysterious incidents. She must face her unbearable past in order to get out of this horrifying paranormal world.

programme.title: We Are Family
programme.desc: Jia-cong, who came from a broken family, and Pei-yi, a single mother who had little talent on the entertainment road, founded a company that can provide "rental family" services.

programme.title: See You Tomorrow
programme.desc: Chen and his partner Guan are legendary navigators, but in the process of helping a girl Xiao Yu, they must also face their own problems.

programme.title: The Moon Thieves
programme.desc: Two young men become involved in a complicated crime involving antique watches.

programme.title: Love After Love
programme.desc: Wei Long travels to HK from Shanghai to pursue her education. As she struggles financially, she becomes her aunts puppet to lure rich men. When Wei Long falls for playboy, George, she sinks in a life of depravity.

programme.title: Cloudy Mountain
programme.desc: When a decade-long tunnel project is about to complete, an earthquake strikes and leads to a series of subsidence, landslides, and put a town nearby are at stake. Will the authority blow up the tunnel?

programme.title: Man On The Edge
programme.desc: The triad gang leader assigns Ah Lok to take charge of the drug trafficking business. However, Ah Lok turns out to be an undercover police officer who unveils a shocking political conspiracy during the investigation.

programme.desc: HBO World Championship Boxing and historic PPV events plus past, current and future World Champions. This episode features Baby Bull, Juan Diaz, (34-2, 17 KOs) battling Paul Malignaggi, aka Magic Man, (26-2, 5 KOs) in a junior welterweight title bout from the Toyota Center in Houston, Texas, USA, on August 22, 2009.

programme.title: Knockouts!: Paul Vs Carlos
programme.desc: The main event in this episode is then-undefeated Paul Williams defending his welterweight championship against Carlos Quintana. The fights result ultimately ended up being what might be considered one of the biggest upsets in boxing.

programme.title: Judo For The World
programme.desc: In this episode, St. Petersburg hosts the season finale where well see the best Judo from some of the sports biggest superstars. Plus, we speak with Academy Award winning actor Adrian Brody and get his impressions of attending his first big Judo event, and we follow 3 Georgian warriors who came to St. Petersburg to finish the year in style.

programme.title: FS MMA: Sonnen Vs McKenzie
programme.desc: MORE MMA MONDAY: Outspoken MMA superstar Chael Sonnen matches up with veteran Tim McKenzie of Stockton, California. McKenzie entered the bout with a record of 10-3, having won his last two fights by TKO over Doug Marshall and Mike McGuinnes. Sonnen was in between stints with the UFC at the time, having won his first two fights with Bodog leading into this one. He would go on to face the likes of Anderson Silva, Jon Jones, and Rashad Evans in the UFC before collecting wins over Rampage Jackson and Wanderlei Silva with Bellator.
